	   <tr><td colspan=2>You're quite right, this is pretty decent for casters.&nbsp;&nbsp;Until I started collecting +hp items on my necro, at level 54, in order to make full efficiency of Lich and Bond of Death (lifetap over time), I had to Lich down to about 2 bubbles of health.  If I lag or time my spells wrong and get hit, when at only 2 bubbles of health, I've got a pretty decent chance of dieing, as once you're below a certain % of health, the mob will definately not leave you alone for your pet, and you're moving slower.  Once I starged getting close to 250 int (Thanks Bazaar!!), I thought I'd do better to swap some items out for +hp items such as this.  Now I can Bond of Death at 3 bubbles of health (having the lifetap wear off just as I hit full health, while Lich'd), and lag and little slipups aren't fatal any longer.  <br><br>99% of the time I'm not fighting something that casts (unless I'm slumming in Najena or something), so -10 mr isn't that hard to suck down.  The only exception is in raid situations, in which case I have resist rings that would replace this item regardless.  So even though it's been said a bunch of times, I'll say it again.  Negative stats don't a worthless item make.  Instead they make a situational item.  Building up situational gear will allow you to be far more powerful in situations when you have the appropriate gear on than a nebulous (all-situation) set of gear would make you.<br>&nbsp;<br>Keleric Medicor<br>Dwarven Cleric, Leader of Peace by Force<br>Skeleric Expirator<br>Gnecromancer<br>Tunare </td></tr>
